The paper deals with the problem of out-of-distribution detection in neural network classifiers, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. The paper proposes a novel algorithm to generate effective OOD samples using a manifold learning network, which falls under the category of deep learning and generative models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the complexity of producing effective OOD samples, which could fall under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CC) or cryptography and security (cs.CR). Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CR are also likely sub-categories.
